The '''Sanrio Virtual Festival''' (サンリオVfes) is a recurring virtual music and culture festival organized by [[wikipedia:Sanrio|Sanrio]] inside [[Special:MyLanguage/VRChat|VRChat]]. The series debuted in December 2021 and has been held annually since, growing from a two-day event to a month-long festival. By January 2026 Sanrio reported more than ten million cumulative visits across the first four editions.<ref name="prtimes-20260114">[https://prtimes.jp/main/html/rd/p/000000709.000037629.html "総来場者数1,000万人超えのVR音楽フェスが今年も開催決定！「Sanrio Virtual Festival 2026」出演アーティスト全28組を発表！"] on ''[https://prtimes.jp PR TIMES]''. Dated January 14, 2026. Retrieved April 8, 2026.</ref>

Each edition features live musical performances by VTubers, virtual artists, and anime tie-in acts, alongside interactive attractions and virtual parades set in Sanrio-themed environments. The festival offers both free and ticketed content and has been accessible across VRChat and, in some years, additional platforms such as REALITY and SPWN.

==Editions==

The ''Sanrio Virtual Festival'' has been held five times from its 2021 debut through 2026. No edition used the year "2022" in its title; the second event took place in January 2023.

