==Sanrio Virtual Festival 2021==

The inaugural edition, officially titled '''''SANRIO Virtual Fes in Sanrio Puroland''''', was held on December 11–12, 2021 as Sanrio's first metaverse event.<ref name="prnewswire-2021" /> The venue was a five-floor underground virtual space beneath a photogrammetry-based recreation of [[wikipedia:Sanrio Puroland|Sanrio Puroland]]. The B2 Luna Stage hosted performances by real-world artists, while the B3 Future Stage presented virtual artists in a 360-degree Sanrio-themed setting. Free areas included the B1 Entry Hall, the B4 Chill Park with a café and mini-live stages, and the B5 ALT3, a PCVR-exclusive club floor directed by 0b4k3.<ref name="panora-2021-preview">[https://panora.tokyo/archives/37702 "サンリオ初のVR音楽フェス「SANRIO Virtual Fes in Sanrio Puroland」先行取材レポート"] on ''[https://panora.tokyo PANORA]''. Retrieved April 10, 2026.</ref>

Over 50 performers appeared across both days, including [[wikipedia:Kizuna_AI|Kizuna AI]], [[wikipedia:Hatsune Miku|Hatsune Miku]], [[wikipedia:AKB48|AKB48]] (Team 8), and CHiCO with HoneyWorks.<ref name="prnewswire-2021" /> Attendees received customizable "Mochipoly" avatars, and high-fiving other players in the paid VRChat area triggered Hello Kitty ribbons.<ref name="prnewswire-2021" /> The event was accessible via VRChat, DOOR, and SPWN across PC, VR headsets, and smartphones.<ref name="prnewswire-2021" />

==Sanrio Virtual Festival 2023==

The second edition, '''''SANRIO Virtual Festival 2023 in Sanrio Puroland''''', ran from January 13 to 22, 2023, with the main music festival on January 21–22.<ref name="prtimes-20230113" /> The lineup grew to 56 performing artists across the returning multi-floor venue, with its Luna Stage, Future Stage, Chill Park, and ALT3 club floor.<ref name="prtimes-2023-timetable">[https://prtimes.jp/main/html/rd/p/000000453.000037629.html "「SANRIO Virtual Festival 2023 in Sanrio Puroland」第二弾出演者&タイムテーブル発表！総勢56組の出演が決定！"] on ''[https://prtimes.jp PR TIMES]''. Retrieved April 10, 2026.</ref>

New for 2023 was Virtual Puro Village, a free area featuring an original "Musical Treasure Hunt" parade with Sanrio characters.<ref name="prtimes-20230113" /><ref name="prtimes-2023-report">[https://prtimes.jp/main/html/rd/p/000000460.000037629.html "「SANRIO Virtual Festival 2023 in Sanrio Puroland」開催レポート"] on ''[https://prtimes.jp PR TIMES]''. Retrieved April 10, 2026.</ref> Performers included Airi Suzuki, SKY-HI, and Non on the real-artist side, alongside virtual acts such as Fuji Aoi, Mirai Akari, and KMNZ.<ref name="prtimes-2023-timetable" /> The event was accessible through VRChat, SPWN, REALITY, and YouTube livestreams for select free content.<ref name="panora-2023">[https://panora.tokyo/archives/60365 "サンリオ、バーチャルイベント「SANRIO Virtual Festival 2023 in Sanrio Puroland」1/13より開催"] on ''[https://panora.tokyo PANORA]''. Retrieved April 10, 2026.</ref>

==Sanrio Virtual Festival 2024==

'''''SANRIO Virtual Festival 2024 in Sanrio Puroland''''' ran from February 19 to March 17, 2024, making it the first month-long edition.<ref name="prtimes-2024-report" /> With 63 artist performances and three new virtual parades, it was the largest edition to date, drawing approximately four million total visitors across all platforms.<ref name="prtimes-2024-report" /> Beyond VRChat, the festival was also accessible via REALITY, ZEPETO, and MetaMe.<ref name="prtimes-2024-smartphone" />

New attractions included interactive games such as "Mochipoli Factory," "Pochacco's Eating Strategy," and "Hello Kitty's Popcorn Machine," as well as a Puro Fashion Garden collaboration with clothing brand Adastria offering 58 items in both physical and digital form.<ref name="prtimes-2024-games">[https://prtimes.jp/main/html/rd/p/000000552.000037629.html "「SANRIO Virtual Festival 2024 in Sanrio Puroland」ゲーム・コラボ企画、アニメ上演コンテンツ追加発表！"] on ''[https://prtimes.jp PR TIMES]''. Retrieved April 10, 2026.</ref> A spin-off '''Summer Edition''' followed from September 13 to 22, 2024, featuring returning content alongside new attractions including a ''Fragaria Memories'' virtual performance and the finals of the SANRIO Virtual Idol Contest.<ref name="prtimes-2024-summer">[https://prtimes.jp/main/html/rd/p/000000590.000037629.html "サンリオによる世界最大級"VRテーマパーク"「SANRIO Virtual Festival 2024 Summer Edition」開催決定！"] on ''[https://prtimes.jp PR TIMES]''. Retrieved April 10, 2026.</ref>

==Sanrio Virtual Festival 2025==

The fourth main edition, '''''Sanrio Virtual Festival 2025''''', ran from February 9 to March 9, 2025 under the theme of "collaboration."<ref name="prtimes-2025-details" /> The lineup bridged multiple VTuber agencies and entertainment spheres, with VShojo's [[wikipedia:Ironmouse|Ironmouse]], NIJISANJI's Tsukino Mito and Higuchi Kaede, hololive's Moona Hoshinova, and Japanese entertainers Matsudaira Ken and Tawara Toshihiko making their VR debut.<ref name="prtimes-2025-details" /><ref name="sanrio-2025-announce">[https://www.sanrio.co.jp/news/digital/mx-v-fes-20241211/ "「Sanrio Virtual Festival 2025」が開催決定♪"] on ''[https://www.sanrio.co.jp Sanrio Co., Ltd.]''. Dated December 11, 2024. Retrieved April 10, 2026.</ref>

New attractions included the virtual parade "RYUGU – Generated Paradise," a boat ride in Virtual Sanrio Puro Land, a fashion garden with collaborative VTuber avatars, and OMI.Cube, a fan-art exhibition space.<ref name="prtimes-2025-details" /> By the conclusion of the 2025 edition, cumulative attendance across the first four festivals had surpassed ten million visitors.<ref name="prtimes-20260114" />

==Virtual Sanrio Puroland==

In December 2025 Sanrio opened '''Virtual Sanrio Puroland''', a permanent VR theme park within VRChat that evolved from the festival series.<ref name="sanrio-puroland">[https://www.sanrio.co.jp/news/digital/mx-virtual-20251211/ "VRテーマパーク「Virtual Sanrio Puroland」がオープン☆｜サンリオ"] on ''[https://www.sanrio.co.jp Sanrio Co., Ltd.]''. Dated December 11, 2025. Retrieved April 8, 2026.</ref> The park launched on December 11, 2025 at 18:00 JST and operates year-round.<ref name="panora-puroland">[https://panora.tokyo/archives/124747 "VRChat上に常設型VRテーマパーク「Virtual Sanrio Puroland」が12/11オープン"] on ''[https://panora.tokyo PANORA]''. Dated December 11, 2025. Retrieved April 9, 2026.</ref> Opening attractions included a collaborative world with [[wikipedia:Kizuna_AI|Kizuna AI]] ("KizunaAI Dream Garden"), an interactive show titled "Spooky 'n' Sweet Mansion," character rooms, and a broadcasting studio ("Virtual Puro Studio") for streamers and VTubers.<ref name="panora-puroland" /> Beginning with the 2026 edition, the festival takes place inside this permanent space rather than a purpose-built temporary venue.<ref name="prtimes-20260114" />

==Sanrio Virtual Festival 2026==

The fifth edition ran from February 8 to March 8, 2026 with 28 performing acts and both free and ticketed content.<ref name="sanrio-20260114">[https://www.sanrio.co.jp/news/digital/mx-v-fes-20260114/ "「Sanrio Virtual Festival 2026」が開催決定☆｜サンリオ"] on ''[https://www.sanrio.co.jp Sanrio Co., Ltd.]''. Dated January 14, 2026. Retrieved April 8, 2026.</ref><ref name="essential-japan-2026">[https://essential-japan.com/news/sanrio-virtual-festival-2026-announces-artist-lineup-and-ticket-sales/ "Sanrio Virtual Festival 2026 Announces Artist Lineup and Ticket Sales"] on ''[https://essential-japan.com Essential Japan]''. Retrieved April 9, 2026.</ref> In March 2026 VRChat noted on Bluesky that the festival was ongoing through March 8 (JST).<ref name="bsky-vfes">[https://bsky.app/profile/vrchat.com/post/3mgb2ovspg22v "#SanrioVfes is ongoing until Mar 8 (JST)!"] on ''[https://bsky.app/profile/vrchat.com Bluesky]''. Dated March 4, 2026. Retrieved April 8, 2026.</ref>

===Concurrent user records===

Virtual concerts featuring Kaguya from the Netflix anime ''[[wikipedia:Cosmic_Princess_Kaguya!|Cosmic Princess Kaguya!]]'' broke VRChat's all-time concurrent user record twice during the festival. On February 15 the platform reached 156,716 concurrent users, surpassing the previous peak of 148,886 set on [[Special:MyLanguage/New Years Eve 2026|New Year's Day 2026]].<ref name="roadtovr-ccu">[https://www.roadtovr.com/vrchat-all-time-high-japanese-concert/ 'VRChat' Breaks All-Time Concurrent User Record with Japanese Anime Concert] on ''[https://www.roadtovr.com Road to VR]''. February 2026. Retrieved April 10, 2026.</ref> The record was broken again on March 8 during the festival's final weekend, reaching a corrected peak of 158,192 concurrent users.<ref name="tupper-bsky-mar8">[https://bsky.app/profile/dtupper.com/post/3mgjfu2hnu22g Tupper (VRChat head of community) on Bluesky]. March 8, 2026. Retrieved April 10, 2026.</ref>

===Activities and features===

New attractions for 2026 included two ''8Puronicles'' virtual parades with story-driven episodes about characters Roy Happy and Palra,<ref name="metacul-parades">[https://metacul-frontier.com/?p=31159 "「Sanrio Vfes 2026」新しいパレードのストーリー性には圧巻。新規パレード『8Puronicles』の先行体験にいってきた"] on ''[https://metacul-frontier.com Metacul Frontier]''. Retrieved April 9, 2026.</ref> a ''SHOW BY ROCK!! WORLD'' based on Sanrio's [[wikipedia:Show by Rock!!|multimedia franchise]],<ref name="metacul-worlds">[https://metacul-frontier.com/?p=31117 "「Sanrio Virtual Festival 2026」先行レポート 新しく増えるワールドをチェック！"] on ''[https://metacul-frontier.com Metacul Frontier]''. Retrieved April 9, 2026.</ref> QuestMaker (an interactive sing-along featuring Hello Kitty, Kogimyun, Hangyodon, and Kiki & Lala), and a camping attraction by orange & MIRA_sk.<ref name="vr-lifemag-sanrio">[https://vr-lifemagazine.com/svfes2026-sanrio/ "【サンリオVfes】キティたちの歌のステージ&参加者みんなとキャンプ！"] on ''[https://vr-lifemagazine.com Virtual Life Magazine]''. Retrieved April 9, 2026.</ref>

